Someone I've never seen or known... I cheated you?

48
00:06:00,050 --> 00:06:02,040
Who are you?

49
00:06:07,370 --> 00:06:10,960
I...  know both of you.

50
00:06:10,960 --> 00:06:15,050
I know you... very well.

51
00:06:15,050 --> 00:06:16,230
Who are you?

52
00:06:16,230 --> 00:06:19,190
So... Who are you?

53
00:06:20,490 --> 00:06:22,360
I am...

54
00:06:22,360 --> 00:06:25,880
Lee Bang Won (son of General Lee Seong Gye).

55
00:06:38,820 --> 00:06:43,440
 8 years ago, Hamjoo 

56
00:06:57,940 --> 00:07:00,440
Bang Won!  It's dangerous.  Do not come!

57
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:04,820
Never you mind, Hyungnim (older brother).
I'm going to catch him.

58
00:07:33,930 --> 00:07:36,650
Ya! Ya!

59
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:53,020
Damn it.

60
00:07:53,020 --> 00:07:55,150
Let's run quickly!

61
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:53,050
Fall backwards, Hyungnim!

62
00:09:23,450 --> 00:09:26,280
  Lee Bang Won   (later King Tae Jong)

63
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:30,290
  Lee Bang Gwa 

64
00:09:34,930 --> 00:09:37,800
 Lee Seong Gye 

65
00:09:37,800 --> 00:09:40,800
Father, father I caught him. 
(Joseon’s first three kings)

66
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:43,470
I said to learn the Gaegyeong language.

67
00:09:44,380 --> 00:09:46,140
Yes!

68
00:09:50,730 --> 00:09:53,330
Tie him up and bring him.

69
00:09:53,330 --> 00:09:55,320
How nice!

70
00:10:05,890 --> 00:10:10,580
Boy, our father sure is a Jantgar!
 Jantgar: The strongest man, in Mongolian .

71
00:10:10,580 --> 00:10:13,980
Again, again... That's Mongolian language.

72
00:10:13,980 --> 00:10:17,780
He says to use neither Mongolian nor Chinese (Beijing dialect), so why do you keep on doing so?

73
00:10:17,780 --> 00:10:20,900
What else should I use to call a Jantgar

74
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:23,040
but exactly that?

75
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:27,520
Doesn't that fit his description the best? Jantgar!

76
00:10:29,010 --> 00:10:30,710
You're right.

77
00:10:30,710 --> 00:10:35,960
If a man like that isn't a Jantgar, then who else would be?

78
00:10:39,010 --> 00:10:43,450
The traitor started to run away.

79
00:10:43,490 --> 00:10:45,830
I ran really hard!

80
00:10:45,830 --> 00:10:47,620
What about Young Master Bang Gwa?

81
00:10:47,620 --> 00:10:50,120
Hyungnim was following me from behind.

82
00:10:50,940 --> 00:10:55,360
Little by little,

83
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:59,450
I caught up to him like the wind, and then suddenly like this—

84
00:11:03,890 --> 00:11:06,070
Bang Won.

85
00:11:10,790 --> 00:11:15,950
Are you going to neglect your studies? Are you?

86
00:11:15,950 --> 00:11:20,090
I don't like to study.

87
00:11:20,090 --> 00:11:23,240
I want to be like you, Father.

88
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:26,480
Like me? What is that?

89
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:31,320
Someone good at archery, riding horses and who wins every battle.

90
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:34,110
Isn't that why people are cheering for you?

91
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:37,520
Isn't that why all the people of this land respect you?

92
00:11:37,520 --> 00:11:40,470
That is why I want to go to battle with you.

93
00:11:40,470 --> 00:11:43,050
Do you have any idea what a war is like?

94
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:46,270
A war?

95
00:11:47,070 --> 00:11:48,410
War is...

96
00:11:48,410 --> 00:11:50,440
Come with me!

97
00:12:00,950 --> 00:12:05,010
Who ordered you to commit this disloyalty?

98
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:14,860
Are you deaf?  ANSWER ME!
 (Lee Ji Ran) 

99
00:12:14,860 --> 00:12:22,690
This is the letter you tried to give to the spy within our group.
 (Ga Byeol Cho: Lee Seong Gye's secret private army) 

100
00:12:22,690 --> 00:12:27,760
Lee In Gyeom sent this. Right?

101
00:12:31,190 --> 00:12:38,080
I'm asking if Prime Minister Lee In Gyeom is the one watching your back?
 Su Shi Joong: the highest ranking political figure in Goryeo 

102
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:40,310
- Beat him up.
- Yes sir!

103
00:12:40,310 --> 00:12:42,360
Enough!

104
00:12:55,470 --> 00:13:00,610
You... You've already betrayed me.

105
00:13:00,610 --> 00:13:07,050
If you reveal who is behind this act then you will be betraying for a second time.

106
00:13:09,230 --> 00:13:13,710
Don't betray anymore.

