a shameless and audacious traitor! Red wolf! Jung Nang!

502
00:48:47,760 --> 00:48:49,570
Jung Nang?

503
00:48:49,570 --> 00:48:51,390
Brother.

504
00:49:04,680 --> 00:49:06,690
It's too high.

505
00:49:09,270 --> 00:49:12,770
Hey! Hurry up and come down!

506
00:49:25,300 --> 00:49:27,300
Hey!

507
00:49:27,300 --> 00:49:29,970
That's the sound of a dog.

508
00:49:35,740 --> 00:49:40,600
This wolf had a real son of a bitch.

509
00:49:40,600 --> 00:49:45,650
It was traitor Shepherd!

510
00:49:50,450 --> 00:49:55,170
 The word shepherd implies Lee Seong Gye's last name, Lee. 

511
00:49:55,940 --> 00:50:03,730
Brother Wolf, the tide has already turned. Surrender now!

512
00:50:03,730 --> 00:50:07,070
Surrender now!!

513
00:50:07,070 --> 00:50:11,320
If you don't surrender, you will die.

514
00:50:11,320 --> 00:50:13,530
You will die.

515
00:50:13,530 --> 00:50:19,000
But if you surrender...

516
00:50:19,000 --> 00:50:21,560
You will die!

517
00:50:22,990 --> 00:50:26,390
I. I am Jung Nang!

518
00:50:29,710 --> 00:50:33,660
Father, what do you mean get rid of Brother Jung Nang?
  (1356, Ssang Seong Colonial Office) 

519
00:50:33,660 --> 00:50:38,330
At Ja Shi (between 11pm - 1am), Goryeo troops will attack us at the Ssang Seong colonial office tomorrow.

520
00:50:38,330 --> 00:50:41,000
You will have to open the gate.

521
00:50:42,700 --> 00:50:44,330
Father!

522
00:50:44,330 --> 00:50:47,860
Yuan will collapse soon. 
 (Lee Ja Choon, Lee Seong Gye's father) 

523
00:50:47,860 --> 00:50:50,870
Then, even now we can persuade Jung Nang.

524
00:50:50,870 --> 00:50:52,980
Don't say the name Jung Nang!

525
00:50:52,980 --> 00:50:56,840
Now he is only an enemy of Goryeo, traitor Jo So Saeng.

526
00:50:56,840 --> 00:50:59,880
If Jo So Saeng is a traitor, then we are too.

527
00:50:59,880 --> 00:51:01,950
Shut your mouth!

528
00:51:03,110 --> 00:51:05,570
Can't you understand?

529
00:51:05,570 --> 00:51:07,960
If we contribute to Goryeo now,

530
00:51:07,960 --> 00:51:11,520
then all of Jo So Saeng's assets will be ours.

531
00:51:11,520 --> 00:51:15,300
I... cannot do it.

532
00:51:15,300 --> 00:51:18,130
As a soldier, I will fight with the Jo family.

533
00:51:18,130 --> 00:51:23,350
Will you really destroy my family line here?

534
00:51:26,250 --> 00:51:27,400
Father!

535
00:51:27,400 --> 00:51:33,190
Our relationship with Jo So Saeng is insignificant. Look at the big goal, Seong Gye

536
00:51:56,850 --> 00:52:01,250
There was a traitor! Some bastard opened the gate!

537
00:52:01,250 --> 00:52:05,970
Since the northern gate is the weakest, we must go through there now!
 Jung Nang Jo So Saeng: head of Ssang Seong colonial office, traitor of Goryeo .

538
00:52:08,660 --> 00:52:11,120
You can't go.

539
00:52:22,860 --> 00:52:25,180
Was it you?

540
00:52:26,270 --> 00:52:28,490
Did you open the gate, Brother?

541
00:52:28,490 --> 00:52:31,040
Don't call me brother.

542
00:52:33,770 --> 00:52:38,850
I did not raise a brother, but a dog.

543
00:52:40,410 --> 00:52:46,430
Your family's lineage is that of a dog who bites its owner.

544
00:53:05,200 --> 00:53:07,140
Goryeo.

545
00:53:08,400 --> 00:53:13,920
What has Goryeo done for your family?

546
00:53:13,920 --> 00:53:17,020
I gave you everything you have.

547
00:53:17,020 --> 00:53:19,100
In the end, you bastards

548
00:53:19,100 --> 00:53:21,600
will also betray Goryeo.

549
00:53:21,600 --> 00:53:23,580
That is...

550
00:53:24,800 --> 00:53:29,940
That is the dirty fate of the dog who betrays his owner.

551
00:53:40,180 --> 00:53:43,620
You dogs of Goryeo.

552
00:53:43,620 --> 00:53:46,920
Your family of dogs that bite their owner's hand will eventually

553
00:53:46,920 --> 00:53:49,340
end up looking like this.

554
00:53:56,040 --> 00:53:59,140
Give me my sword.

555
00:54:16,210 --> 00:54:19,590
Hey! What are you doing? Why aren't you cutting his head off?

556
00:54:19,590 --> 00:54:23,210
Take my sword!

557
00:54:42,210 --> 00:54:44,580
I got rid of my enemy!

558
00:54:44,580 --> 00:54:46,770
I got rid of him!

559
00:55:15,790 --> 00:55:18,930
Did you enjoy the play?

560
00:55:19,590 --> 00:55:24,210
Gaegyeong people are good at laughing about nothing.

561
00:55:24,210 --> 00:55:27,950
Since you betrayed Jo So Saeng, someone like your own brother,

562
00:55:27,950 --> 00:55:31,630
it must be painful for you.

563
00:55:32,510 --> 00:55:37,450
We prepared in a hurry so we used swords.

564
00:55:37,450 --> 00:55:42,190
Originally it was an arrow, wasn't it? Since you are a god-sent archer.

565
00:55:43,900 --> 00:55:47,220
It's alright, General Lee.

566
00:55:47,220 --> 00:55:53,180
You must have had a good reason for what you did.

567
00:55:53,180 --> 00:55:59,640
Of course General Choi Young, and nobles who value loyalty over life,

568
00:55:59,640 --> 00:56:03,770
might think differently.

569
00:56:03,770 --> 00:56:08,820
In order to play out this hand, did you plant a mole in Hamjoo?

570
00:56:08,820 --> 00:56:14,730
I never planted any spies in Hamjoo.

571
00:56:14,730 --> 00:56:17,890
LOOK HERE, Prime Minister!

572
00:56:20,200 --> 00:56:23,960
Now I understand

573
00:56:25,560 --> 00:56:29,740
why you throw yourself into countless battles, risking your life.

574
00:56:29,740 --> 00:56:32,730
You're generous to people, without limit.

575
00:56:32,730 --> 00:56:39,270
So, why didn't you have a goal to enter Gaegyeong?

576
00:56:40,190 --> 00:56:42,870
Why?

577
00:56:42,870 --> 00:56:47,550
What ambition does he have to live that way?

578
00:56:51,600 --> 00:56:54,640
Now, I understand.

579
00:56:59,240 --> 00:57:06,320
It was because, more than anyone else, you can't forgive yourself.

580
00:57:08,210 --> 00:57:10,840
But...

581
00:57:10,840 --> 00:57:13,540
Why, now, are you trying to forgive yourself?

582
00:57:13,540 --> 00:57:15,730
Why, now, are you getting involved in politics?

583
00:57:15,730 --> 00:57:17,150
Why right at this moment?

584
00:57:17,150 --> 00:57:18,820
Why are you blocking my path?

585
00:57:18,820 --> 00:57:21,270
Why!

586
00:57:36,270 --> 00:57:38,510
Does anyone else

587
00:57:39,350 --> 00:57:41,590
know about this?

588
00:57:41,590 --> 00:57:43,490
Nobody else knows

589
00:57:43,490 --> 00:57:48,290
whether it will be secret between us or not.

590
00:57:55,950 --> 00:57:58,470
What are you going to do?

591
00:58:17,310 --> 00:58:19,240
Please

592
00:58:20,650 --> 00:58:23,460
look the other way this time.

593
00:58:25,720 --> 00:58:27,600
I beg you.

